        textProvided: "[{28 note 19}: Walter Hooper, in <i>CL</i> 3:1255 note 94, mentions that “Reply to Mr. R” was “a paper originally read to the Socratic Club,” later rewritten and published as “Myth Became Fact.” Hooper was probably referring to Bodleian MS Facs.b.90, fols.114-120, entitled]<br><br>In Reply to Mr. R.<br><br>[with the hand-written subtitle:]<br><br>A Paper read to the Socratic Club.<br><br>[{38 note 20} In the typescript mentioned in the previous note, [A.L.] Rowse’s name appears on fol. 116 in the sentence:]<br><br>For thoughts, as Mr <strike>Rowse</strike> R. said, move with the times<br><br>[with “Rowse” crossed out and replaced by “R.” in Lewis’s hand.]",
