        textProvided: "Magdalen College, Oxford<br>Nov. 23 / 54<br><br>Dear Joan,<br><br>I am haunted by a feeling that I have been asked to a big tea-fight next Mon. before my lecture, but can find nothing about it in my files. As you and Stanley [Bennett] wd. almost certainly be asked, can you tell me? (I’m <i>not</i> mixing it up with a sherry-party <i>after</i> the lecture given by [Basil] Willey). Oh dear, what a scrape! Not being one yourself, you can’t imagine how difficult life is if one is a fool!<br><br>Yours<br>C.S. Lewis<br><br>P.S. Reply at Magdalen<u>e</u> will find me from to-morrow.",
