        title: "Letter to Geoffrey Shepherd (20 January 1960)",
        printedIn: "Steve Beebe and Joel Heck, “C.S. Lewis’s Role as General Editor of <i>Nelson’s Medieval and Renaissance Library Series</i>” in <i>SEVEN: An Anglo-American Literary Review</i>",
        issueOrVolume: "vol. 39",
        pageRange: "42",
        year: 2023,
        monthAndDay: null,
        textProvided: "Magdalene College, Cambridge<br>20 Jan 1960<br><br>Dear Shepherd<br><br>I can’t promise to be very quick, so if haste is imperative, you’ll have to go on without my verdict. But of course I’ll look at the MS. as soon as I’ve time and make any comments that occur to me, realizing that, by then, there will be the question of rejection.<br><br>All good wishes,<br>Yours<br>C.S. Lewis",
        type: "Letter",
        notes: null
