        printedIn: "Steve Beebe and Joel Heck, “C.S. Lewis’s Role as General Editor of <i>Nelson’s Medieval and Renaissance Library Series</i>” in <i>SEVEN: An Anglo-American Literary Review</i>",
        issueOrVolume: "vol. 39",
        pageRange: "43",
        year: 2023,
        monthAndDay: null,
        textProvided: "Dear Shepherd<br><br>Look again and I think you will find that the two bulky packets I sent you contain all the TS-FL as well as AL.<br><br>Pearsall must have his references to <i>Generides</i> if he wants, of course. I am staggered by the ascription of it and AL to a single author. A very versatile poet! I don’t myself believe that verbal parallels can even begin to prove it. The same method wd. prove that nearly all English critical work for the past 20 years was by one man. However, <i>vive le sport</i>.<br><br>Yours<br>C.S. Lewis",
        type: "Letter",
